@danrobinson @0xstark @VladZamfir @coindesk @mikejcasey That's my definition of "layer 2 scaling solution" :)

A *state channel* is a layer 2 scaling solution whers the expected outcome can be updated with zero on-chain operations.

Plasma requires publishing the merkle root, so it's a different category of thing.

@interfluidity @jp_koning The arguments that *do* make sense are:

